cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CG, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the computational complexity of a puzzle game, which suggests it may fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of an integer lattice and the manipulation of blocks suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The puzzle involves an agent making decisions, which could be seen as an artificial intelligence problem (cs.AI). The sliding of blocks and the movement between start and goal positions could be related to computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the proof of NP-hardness involves reduction from SAT, which could be related to graph theory (cs.GT).
